		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My elementary school (N. Vancouver, B.C.) had era-appropriate Commodore PETs that we used for LOGO programming during the very occasional &quot;computer class&quot;, which in the late-80s were replaced with era-appropriate Mac 512Ks.<br /><br />One elementary school in the same area had it good -- their computer room was stocked at the time with Amiga 1000s, on which they had paint &amp; artwork lessons, a classmate once told me when we were all together in the same Jr. high school.

		

		</td>
